The paper deals with the problem of bin packing, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from discrepancy theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that deals with the distribution of objects in a set, and thus the paper could also be classified under cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also presents an approximation algorithm, which involves analyzing the combinatorial structure of the problem, and thus could be classified under cs.GT (graph theory). The paper also uses linear programming techniques, which is a subfield of optimization and could be classified under cs.IT (information theory). Finally, the paper presents an improvement over a previous algorithm, which involves analyzing the performance of the algorithm, and thus could be classified under cs.LG (machine learning).
